result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Karole L. Whitrock

records.addlTxt:
Cases called at 10:00 AM: 21CF1344, 21CM997, 22CM320, 22CM565.
Defendant Karole L. Whitrock in court, in custody with Attorney David W. Field.  Deputy District Attorney Angela Beranek in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Agreement has been reached. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
21CM997: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 3 as charged in the Criminal Complaint and is sentenced to Court Costs/surcharges, Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
22CM320: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1 as charged in the Criminal Complaint and is sentenced to Court Costs/surcharges, Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
21CF1344: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1 as charged in the Information. Sentence is Withheld and the Defendant is placed on 2 Years of Probation with the following conditions:
60 Days of Jail with Huber (Stayed pending further order of the Court). Maintain absolute sobriety. No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting. 
Restitution in the amount of $504.85 (inclusive of the 10% surcharge) Joint and Several with co-defendant in 21CM997.
Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. Court Costs/surcharges. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
Remaining charges are dismissed and read in.

11:03 AM case called. Prosecuting attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Karole L. Whitrock appeared by video, in custody with Attorney Rachel Robole. 
Waives reading of the complaint. Settlement Conference (by phone) with District Attorney's Office (715-839-4828) on 7-25-22 at 1:45 PM. Return to court: 8-15-22 at 9:30 AM.
